      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "The American Imams Academy demonstrates a high level of financial discipline regarding its overhead. By maintaining <cite id=\"8\">zero fundraising expenses</cite>, the organization ensures that contributions are not diluted by marketing or solicitation costs. This lean operation is paired with a <cite id=\"11\">3-year revenue CAGR of 11.9%</cite>, indicating steady growth in community support. Furthermore, the academy has built a significant safety net, holding <cite id=\"12\">$2,195,479 in total assets</cite> against relatively low liabilities, which allows it to weather economic fluctuations while continuing its specialized educational tracks."
      ],
      "summary": "The American Imams Academy (AIA) is a specialized educational institution dedicated to training the next generation of Muslim community leaders in the United States. The organization provides <cite id=\"1\">higher education in Islamic theology and Da\u2019wah</cite> to develop qualified imams and scholars. AIA operates several academic tracks, including a <cite id=\"2\">Bachelor\u2019s in Islamic Theology and Da\u2019wah</cite> and a <cite id=\"3\">2-Year Associate\u2019s Degree</cite> program. Beyond formal degrees, the academy offers a <cite id=\"4\">Quranic Arabic Program</cite> and specialized <cite id=\"5\">Imam License</cite> training. Financially, the organization reported <cite id=\"6\">total revenue of $824,033</cite> in 2023. The academy maintains a <cite id=\"7\">program expense ratio of 70.2%</cite>, ensuring that the majority of donor funds directly support its educational mission. Notably, the organization demonstrates <cite id=\"8\">exceptional fundraising efficiency of $0.00 per $1 raised</cite>, meaning it does not spend donor money on professional fundraising solicitations. While the academy serves a critical niche in domestic leadership development, it currently holds a <cite id=\"9\">low data confidence rating</cite> due to limited public transparency and third-party evaluations.",
